Hi.

I've observed that the check added for revision 1.12 to HoldsOptions:

if(option.getParent() != this)
	throw new IllegalArgumentException();

Fails whenever an attempt to restore defaults is made.  Removing this check allows options to be restored to their default value.  I just thought I'd warn you, although it might be caused by my own changes elsewhere.

Chris Mead.
